For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO AMEND THE HEALTHCARE CONTRACTING
10 SIMPLIFICATION ACT; TO MODIFY THE DEFINITION OF
11 "HEALTHCARE INSURER" UNDER THE HEALTHCARE CONTRACTING
12 SIMPLIFICATION ACT; TO CLARIFY THE PROHIBITION ON
13 LEASING A HEALTHCARE CONTRACT OR PROVIDER NETWORK;
14 AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
15
16
Subtitle
17
18 TO AMEND THE HEALTHCARE CONTRACTING
19 SIMPLIFICATION ACT.
20
21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
22
23 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 23-99-1202(7), concerning the definition of
24 "health insurer" under the Healthcare Contracting Simplification Act, is
25 amended to read as follows:
26 (7)(A) "Healthcare insurer" means an entity that is subject to
27 state insurance regulation and provides or administers health insurance in
28 this state.
29 (B) "Healthcare insurer" includes:
30 (i) An insurance company;
31 (ii) A health maintenance organization;
32 (iii) A hospital and medical service corporation;
33 (iv) A risk-based provider organization;
34 (v) A sponsor of a nonfederal self-funded
35 governmental plan; and
36 (vi) A dental-only plan; and
*ANS074*
