1 (vii) A third-party administrator or other entity
2 acting on behalf of a self-insured health benefit plan;
3
4 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code § 23-99-1203(a), concerning the prohibited
5 activities under the Healthcare Contracting Simplification Act, is amended to
6 read as follows:
7 (a) Except as provided in subsections (b) and (d) of this section, a
8 contracting entity shall not:
9 (1) Offer to a healthcare provider a healthcare contract that
10 includes an all-products clause;
11 (2) Enter into a healthcare contract with a healthcare provider
12 that includes an all-products clause; or
13 (3) Amend or renew an existing healthcare contract previously
14 entered into with a healthcare provider so that the healthcare contract as
15 amended or renewed adds or continues to include an all-products clause; or
16 (4) Enforce a stipulation, requirement, or policy that has the
17 effect of an all-products clause whether or not an all-products clause is
18 included in the healthcare contract.
19
20 SECTION 3. Arkansas Code § 23-99-1210 is amended to read as follows:
21 23-99-1210. Healthcare contract or provider network — Prohibition.
22 (a) A healthcare insurer contracting entity shall not:
23 (1) Lease, rent, or sell a healthcare contract or provider
24 network of a health benefit plan to another contracting entity, healthcare
25 insurer, or third-party administrator; or
26 (2) In any manner allow the use of a healthcare contract or
27 provider network of a health benefit plan by another contracting entity,
28 healthcare insurer, or third-party administrator.
29 (b)(1) A violation of this section is:
30 (A) An unfair trade practice under § 23-66-206; and
31 (B) Subject to the Trade Practices Act, § 23-66-201 et
32 seq.
33 (2) If a healthcare contract contains a provision that violates
34 this section, then the provision under the healthcare contract is void.
35 (c) This section does not apply if:
36 (1) a healthcare insurer: A contracting entity is a dental-only
